main event: A bright object larger than a star was observed in Kansas City, Missouri, moving with a sudden burst of speed and then disappearing.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 15 minutes,The object appeared star-like with a trailing pattern and was bright,Two separate observations noted similar characteristics of bright, fast-moving objects in the sky,No photographs were taken of the incident,The report concludes insufficient information to identify the object.
sighted object: a bright object resembling a star
